  "text": "Two evaluators were trained in the correct scoring of the FLACC (Face, Legs, Activity, Cry, Consolability [CITATION_1] ) scale and underwent an interrater reliability evaluation. A video recording of each patient was used to score the FLACC scale during the anesthetic procedure. The evaluators were blind to the patients' group membership.",
